This fresh and bright image of a simple table we shot with @jessicadelaneyphotography for our shop made me smile today as we head into another day of battling this nasty virus. Being this sick over the holidays, having to cancel plans and trying to take care of the kids while we feel so ill has really put a damper on my (already relatively pessimistic, let’s be honest) spirit. Watching people on IG on their happy ski and beach vacations, toasting the holidays, enjoying time with their kids… it’s kinda killing me. But I also know that so many of you are in the same boat as us and like everything in life, this is all temporary and perhaps a lesson in letting go of control, in stopping the cycle of comparison and just focus on my own little family and what we need to do to be healthy and happy. Worry less about optics and “keeping up”and more about finding joy. Someone remind me of this once I feel better 😂

Looking back on this install and shoot at our Concord, MA project reminds me that, while we love antique homes, your house doesn’t have to be built in the 19th century to FEEL timeless, layered and lived in… Here’s how we do it ↓
• All about the mix
Every space should have a mix of old and new - think Facebook marketplace finds or family heirlooms next to a crisp new upholstered chair

• Play with color
While there’s a time and a place for an all-neutral space, there’s something about the use of color in this room that feels playful but not too trendy.

• Texture is everything
We always make sure to incorporate wood tones, upholstery, antique rugs and other textured elements to add interest. By layering these on top of one another, we’re able to achieve a unique, enveloping space that feels like home.

Dorset is a beautifully crafted collection based on Erin Gates most beloved vintage rug finds. Each design exudes warmth and character that celebrates a different traditional style. From Bokhara geometric patterns, to Indian inspired paisley’s, Dorset honors historic antique rug styles, while accomplishing a major achievement in printed technology. Made of 100% polyester chenille, and developed using a unique heat set printed technology, this collection is soft, low pile, and absolutely timeless. There are no faux filters applied to these printed rugs. Every single knot is accounted for and every pixel of color represents the authentic craftsmanship of a beautiful hand-knotted vintage rug.

( DORSET - 1 GREY )
